Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated) and @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @green chilli{1}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped). Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced). Halve the @red pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded, chopped into small pieces). Trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and cut into thirds).

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for your rice. When boiling, stir in the @brown basmati rice{150%g} and @cardamom pod{1} and cook for ~{25%minutes}. When cooked, drain the rice thoroughly in a #sieve{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat.

> Add more water if it starts to evaporate too much.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the mushrooms and stir-fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #bowl{} and set aside. Return the pan to medium heat (add a drizzle of oil if it's dry). Add the onion and pepper and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the ginger, garlic, a pinch of @chilli{pinch} (careful - you can add more later!), the @ground turmeric{1%tsp}, @ground cumin{2%tsp} and @ground coriander{1%tsp}.

Cook for another ~{1%minute} then stir in the @red split lentils{50%g}, @finely chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped) and @water{250%ml}. Bring to the boil, cover with a #lid{} then reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened and the lentils are soft, stirring occasionally, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir in the green beans for the final ~{8%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water if the curry looks too dry.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1%sprig}(roughly chopped, stalks and leaves). Pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} in a bowl and stir through half the chopped coriander and as much or as little of the remaining chilli as you like.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and remove the cardamom pods. Stir the mushrooms, @garam masala{1%tsp} and remaining chopped coriander through the curry. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Serve the rice in #bowls{} topped with the curry and a dollop of the coriander chilli yoghurt. Enjoy!